-- Taiwan Equity Movers: Catcher, Powertech, Rexchip Electronics
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-03-01T05:51:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-01/taiwan-equity-movers-catcher-powerchip-powertech-rexchip.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The benchmark Taiex Index lost less than 0.1 percent to
8,118.34.  Catcher Technology Co. (2474)  (2474 TT) gained 3.7 percent to
NT$223.50, the highest close since Sept. 13. Citigroup Inc.
raised its 2012 earnings estimates for Catcher by 5 percent, on
new products that will be rolled out in the second quarter,
according to a report today. The bank raised its share-price
estimate 34 percent to NT$266 and kept the stock at “buy.”  Powertech Technology Inc. (6239)  (6239 TT) slumped 7 percent to
NT$62.70, the second day the company sank by its daily limit.
The stock was cut to “sell” from “neutral” at SinoPac
Securities Corp. The company has NT$4.5 billion in accounts
receivable from  Japan ’s Elpida Memory Inc., which filed for
bankruptcy.  Rexchip Electronics Corp. (4932)  (4932 TT) rallied 6.7 percent to
NT$7.80.  Powerchip Technology Corp. (5346)  will help Rexchip sell its
products, Powerchip Chairman Frank Huang said in a briefing
yesterday. Rexchip, a venture of Elpida Memory Inc., which filed
for bankruptcy, sank 31 percent yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
